and asked the bartender for a drink,

10:17.291 --> 10:18.907
and the bartender said, "Man, I tell you,

10:18.907 --> 10:20.641
you've got a problem don't you?"

10:20.641 --> 10:22.850
And the frog said, "yeah, I sure do-"

10:22.850 --> 10:23.787
- [Sukie] I'll see you late Dave.

10:23.787 --> 10:27.968
"Can you cut this wart
off my ass?" (laughs)

10:29.129 --> 10:30.508
- And, God, can that man talk.

10:30.508 --> 10:31.666
(upbeat dramatic music)

10:31.666 --> 10:33.977
Bars and restaurants in a
vibrant college town like this

10:33.977 --> 10:37.168
are always packed at lunchtime,
but this place is dead!

10:37.168 --> 10:38.284
- [Lindsey] I'm Lindsey.
- [Gordon] How are you?

10:38.284 --> 10:39.962
- Good! There you go!
- Thank you.

10:39.962 --> 10:41.391
- Can I get you something to drink?

10:41.391 --> 10:43.052
- Do you have some ice-cold water, please?

10:43.052 --> 10:44.820
- Okay, mm-hmm.

10:44.820 --> 10:47.063
- Thank you, my darling,
what would you recommend?

10:47.063 --> 10:49.743
- Strawberry field sushI is very popular,

10:49.743 --> 10:51.026
it's a little bit sweeter.

10:51.026 --> 10:52.277
- I'll try it.
- [Lindsey] Okay.

10:52.277 --> 10:55.288
- Las Vegas as an appetiser
as well. And then...

10:55.288 --> 10:58.561
Oh, the sakura, five individual
rolls rolled into one.

10:58.561 --> 11:00.233
(cash register creaking)

11:00.233 --> 11:02.795
(gentle music)

11:02.795 --> 11:07.323
