- The Las Vegas.

12:34.838 --> 12:35.706
- Ooh, oh my God, cream cheese?

12:35.706 --> 12:38.498
- Salmon, cream cheese and
asparagus, then it's deep-fried

12:38.498 --> 12:41.188
and comes with jalapenos.

12:41.188 --> 12:43.308
- Fried salmon with cream cheese.

12:44.690 --> 12:48.028
(Gordon munching)

12:48.028 --> 12:51.000
Disgusting.
(upbeat dramatic music)

12:51.000 --> 12:52.386
What a strange combination,

12:52.386 --> 12:53.742
very weird, it doesn't
work for me, that one.

12:53.742 --> 12:56.935
I mean, it's just greasy.

12:56.935 --> 12:58.236
- And get this out of the way?

12:58.236 --> 12:59.748
- As quick as possible.
- Okay.

12:59.748 --> 13:02.113
- [Gordon] Thank you.
- You're welcome.

13:02.113 --> 13:03.064
- It's dreadful.

13:03.064 --> 13:04.930
My first impressions of the food here

13:04.930 --> 13:06.727
is that it's as bad as the rooms.

13:06.727 --> 13:09.114
(upbeat dramatic music)

13:09.114 --> 13:10.591
- [Sukie] Sakura.

13:11.695 --> 13:15.246
- [Lindsey] Sakura and there's
cream cheese in the middle.

13:16.682 --> 13:17.651
- Look at that thing.

13:17.651 --> 13:19.758
So it's pretty big, right?

13:19.758 --> 13:21.909
so how are you supposed
to get it in your mouth?

13:22.823 --> 13:24.575
- I've never eaten it before.

13:24.575 --> 13:26.264
- Let's try, come on.

13:26.264 --> 13:28.350
- Me?
- We're in this together.

13:28.350 --> 13:30.357
- Oh, no, you ordered
this one all on your own.

13:30.357 --> 13:34.700
- That's yours there,
ready? Open wide, please.

13:34.700 --> 13:35.909
- [Lindsey] Wait, there is no way

13:35.909 --> 13:37.181
this is gonna fit in my mouth.

13:37.181 --> 13:38.947
- Ready? One, two, three.

13:40.354 --> 13:42.614
Ah.
- Uh-uh, I can't do it.

13:43.903 --> 13:44.918
- Now I know how my granddad feels

13:44.918 --> 13:47.848
when he puts his new teeth
in. (Lindsey chuckles)

13:47.848 --> 13:49.548
- Can I throw it away now?

13:49.548 --> 13:52.937
- Yeah. So you took one little bite?

13:52.937 --> 13:54.031
- [Lindsey] I did.

13:54.031 --> 13:57.191
- Damn, disaster, total disaster.

13:57.191 --> 13:58.849
How did it taste, by the way?

13:58.849 --> 13:59.717
- Not very good.

14:00.621 --> 14:02.957
The sakura was very chewy.

14:02.957 --> 14:06.231
Sukie does try her best,
but she has no idea

14:06.231 --> 14:07.722
what she's doing.

14:07.722 --> 14:10.882
- What's wrong with the
sakura, bland, ugly, bad?

14:10.882 --> 14:13.561
- Chewy, strange combination.

14:13.561 --> 14:15.021
- Chewy?

14:15.021 --> 14:18.149
- Yep, and impossible
to put in your mouth.

14:18.149 --> 14:19.953
- Let me tell you about my sushi,

14:19.953 --> 14:23.050
I'm not a morimoto or
nobu, absolutely not,

14:23.050 --> 14:26.105
I'm doing my best and I respect rice.

14:26.105 --> 14:27.200
- [Gordon] What is this one?

14:27.200 --> 14:28.243
- [Lindsey] Strawberry field.

14:28.243 --> 14:31.416
- Man, look at that, strawberry on sushi.

14:33.603 --> 14:35.354
On behalf of every
Japanese chef in America,

14:35.354 --> 14:37.930
I'd like to apologise, it's very weird.

14:37.930 --> 14:39.001
- [Lindsey] Which part
is so terribly weird?

14:39.001 --> 14:42.257
- Just you wouldn't cover
white tuna with strawberries

14:42.257 --> 14:43.195
and then glaze it.

14:45.364 --> 14:48.913
Strawberry fields, I'd
rather fucking eat a beatle.

14:48.913 --> 14:52.110
(gentle upbeat music)

14:52.110 --> 14:55.343
- It's too sweet, strawberries
don't belong with tuna.

14:55.343 --> 14:59.339
- I am frustrated that Gordon
does not like my sushi.

14:59.339 --> 15:01.746
I've tried all I can.

15:01.746 --> 15:04.191
(gentle upbeat music)

15:04.191 --> 15:06.411
- How are you doing, honeybun?

15:06.411 --> 15:08.377
- [Sukie] Oh, he doesn't like any.

15:08.377 --> 15:09.847
- He doesn't like any of it?

15:09.847 --> 15:12.975
- No.
(David laughs)

15:12.975 --> 15:16.176
- So, truthfully, what
is wrong with this place?

15:16.176 --> 15:17.386
- Lack of business.

15:17.386 --> 15:19.690
- So, on an average weekend,
how many guests would you do?

15:19.690 --> 15:22.245
- On a busy weekend maybe 12 people.

15:22.245 --> 15:23.944
- Are they in-house
guests, the hotel guests?

15:23.944 --> 15:25.123
- [Lindsey] Usually.

15:25.123 --> 15:27.291
- So virtually, nobody from the outside?

15:27.291 --> 15:28.160
- [Lindsey] Correct.

15:28.160 --> 15:31.911
- Jesus. Anyway, where are the owners?

15:31.911 --> 15:33.127
Can you tell me where they are?

15:33.127 --> 15:34.029
- Sure!

15:34.029 --> 15:35.758
- Thank you.

15:35.758 --> 15:38.928
- They've got just 36
bedrooms, yet on a busy night,

15:38.928 --> 15:41.076
just 12 guests eat here.

15:41.076 --> 15:43.846
With food that bad, I'm not surprised.

15:43.846 --> 15:45.268
(upbeat dramatic music)

15:45.268 --> 15:48.563
Congratulations on the
longest lunch I've ever had

15:48.563 --> 15:53.373
in my entire cooking
career, that was 97 minutes,

15:54.642 --> 15:55.778
and half of it was raw.

15:55.778 --> 15:59.157
As a novice cook, why are
you making sushi? It's crazy!

15:59.157 --> 16:03.849
- I'm trying my best to at
least introduce Mississippi,

16:03.849 --> 16:05.267
let's eat a little bit healthier.

16:05.267 --> 16:07.206
- There's nothing healthier with my lunch.

16:07.206 --> 16:08.405
Maybe a health warning.

16:09.740 --> 16:12.409
Surely you should be giving
the locals what they wanna eat,

16:12.409 --> 16:13.692
that's why they come.

16:13.692 --> 16:15.962
Well, talking to Lindsey,
the only customers we get now

16:15.962 --> 16:17.571
are the ones staying in the hotel,

16:17.571 --> 16:21.804
which is practically no one!
The business is on its arse.

16:21.804 --> 16:23.934
And how much debt are you in?

16:24.891 --> 16:27.073
- Over $900,000.

16:27.073 --> 16:28.961
- $900,000?

16:28.961 --> 16:31.060
- Right.

16:31.060 --> 16:32.575
- We are in debt?

16:32.575 --> 16:34.348
- Please don't say you don't know.

16:35.633 --> 16:38.630
(upbeat music)

16:38.630 --> 16:40.281
(electricity buzzing)

16:40.281 --> 16:43.221
So far, Starkville,
Mississippi's Hotel Chester

16:43.221 --> 16:44.723
has been a massive letdown.

16:44.723 --> 16:46.871
Hotel Chester entrance, wow.

16:46.871 --> 16:49.999
Such a huge building and such a tiny sign.

16:49.999 --> 16:52.095
The dated, soulless rooms are awful.

16:52.095 --> 16:54.556
It's like a cheap motel chain!

16:54.556 --> 16:58.740
Strawberry on sushi. The sushI
is the worst I've ever had.

16:59.785 --> 17:00.653
That is hideous.

17:00.653 --> 17:02.595
And David, the co-owner,
has just admitted to me

17:02.595 --> 17:06.102
and to his wife that they're
almost $1 million in debt.

17:06.102 --> 17:06.970
$900,000?

17:07.864 --> 17:08.732
- Right.

17:10.113 --> 17:10.982
- We are in debt?

17:10.982 --> 17:12.765
- Please don't say you don't know.

17:15.170 --> 17:19.209
- I'm deeply sorry and
I'm sad that you're upset.

17:20.425 --> 17:21.875
- I'm not upset at you.

17:21.875 --> 17:26.775
David should not have been
hiding the financial status

17:26.775 --> 17:27.644
from me.

17:28.663 --> 17:30.654
- [Gordon] Finding out
she's been kept in the dark

17:30.654 --> 17:32.406
has angered Sukie.

17:32.406 --> 17:35.086
- Dave, I don't know what we are doing!

17:35.086 --> 17:39.048
I do the spending side and
you do the paying side!

17:39.048 --> 17:41.509
- I don't share the finances with Sukie-

17:41.509 --> 17:42.844
- This is getting ridiculous.

17:42.844 --> 17:45.388
- 'Cause I'm afraid of
hurting Sukie's feelings.

17:45.388 --> 17:46.535
Calm down.

17:46.535 --> 17:48.120
- No, I'm not gonna calm down.

17:48.120 --> 17:49.579
- [Gordon] While the owners argue,

17:49.579 --> 17:51.196
guests who have heard about my visit

17:51.196 --> 17:52.968
are arriving at the Chester.

17:52.968 --> 17:54.366
- For dinner you're just
gonna go to the restaurant

17:54.366 --> 17:57.706
which is just a straight shoot
right back there, all right?

17:57.706 --> 17:58.575
- Okay.
- Thank you.

17:58.575 --> 18:00.465
- And tonight, the restaurant and hotel

18:00.465 --> 18:02.822
will be full of people for
the first time in years.

18:02.822 --> 18:04.793
I feel sorry for all of them.

18:04.793 --> 18:06.388
How long have you actually been waiting?

18:06.388 --> 18:07.639
- I would say at least 45 minutes.

18:07.639 --> 18:10.069
- 45 minutes, my apologies.

18:10.069 --> 18:11.612
- How long have you
been waiting? I'm sorry.

18:11.612 --> 18:12.665
- We've been here about an hour.

18:12.665 --> 18:14.137
- [Gordon] An hour.

18:14.137 --> 18:15.319
- Mm.
- Yeah.

18:15.319 --> 18:16.187
- I'm sorry.

18:16.187 --> 18:17.993
I've never seen anything like this before,

18:17.993 --> 18:19.922
it's insane how long
these guests are waiting.

18:19.922 --> 18:22.167
So what table's this Sukie?

18:25.553 --> 18:26.905
- Oh, pardon me, I'm sorry?

18:26.905 --> 18:28.817
- No, I just asked what
table you're doing?

18:28.817 --> 18:32.428
- The very first table.

18:33.926 --> 18:35.427
- It's been well over an hour

18:35.427 --> 18:38.535
and Sukie is only working
on the first table.

18:38.535 --> 18:41.371
She's really struggling and
yet David's not stepping in

18:41.371 --> 18:42.239
to lend a hand.

18:42.239 --> 18:45.719
(upbeat dramatic music)

18:45.719 --> 18:49.525
So, you know, over an hour in to service,

18:49.525 --> 18:51.631
would you go in and help her?

18:51.631 --> 18:55.932
I would but, that's just not
my territory, unfortunately.

18:55.932 --> 19:00.192
- Right, it's like the hotel's
falling apart around you.

19:00.192 --> 19:02.726
If someone needs you in
the kitchen, in the bar,

19:02.726 --> 19:05.176
the reception, shouldn't
you be multitasking?

19:05.176 --> 19:06.636
- The kitchen is her territory.

19:06.636 --> 19:08.520
- Okay, well, I'm just
asking, it's your hotel.

19:08.520 --> 19:10.228
- No, I know and I appreciate that.

19:10.228 --> 19:11.213
- [Gordon] Yeah.

19:11.213 --> 19:13.205
If the kitchen's not David's territory

19:13.205 --> 19:14.553
then maybe the rooms are.

19:16.779 --> 19:17.648
- I touched the blinds and
there's dust all over it.

19:17.648 --> 19:20.168
- [Guest] Squalor, it's hard.

19:21.341 --> 19:22.568
- There's a beat-up family.

19:22.568 --> 19:24.768
It's like it came out of
someone's house when they died.

19:24.768 --> 19:27.365
- This is definitely not a
place I'd wanna hang out.

19:27.365 --> 19:29.388
- [Gordon] It seems to me
that David has checked out.

19:29.388 --> 19:31.848
I don't understand what's going on here.

19:31.848 --> 19:33.392
- This is not good, okay?

19:33.392 --> 19:35.112
- [Gordon] Sukie is
totally out of her depth,

19:35.112 --> 19:36.530
having only dealt with one

19:36.530 --> 19:39.484
of the eight tables waiting
for food. Jesus Christ.

19:39.484 --> 19:42.578
- Oh, no, this is awful!

19:42.578 --> 19:45.039
- Mom?
- Wow. What's wrong, darling?

19:45.039 --> 19:46.825
- They said it wasn't cooked.

19:48.105 --> 19:51.858
- Yep, it's cold. Yeah,
that needs more cooking.

19:51.858 --> 19:53.036
- Mom?

19:53.036 --> 19:54.020
- What's wrong?

19:54.911 --> 19:56.475
- It's not cooked.

19:57.431 --> 19:59.893
- [Gordon] You okay?

19:59.893 --> 20:03.746
- [Meghan] I don't even
wanna get her in trouble.

20:03.746 --> 20:05.362
- Why has she burst into tears?

20:06.581 --> 20:08.260
You okay?
- [Meghan] I'm fine.

20:08.260 --> 20:09.507
- Help me understand. what's going on?

20:09.507 --> 20:11.013
- No, I just-

20:11.013 --> 20:11.881
- The fish is undercooked in the centre.

20:11.881 --> 20:15.098
- I know, it's just I don't-

20:15.098 --> 20:17.926
- Don't what? What is it?

20:17.926 --> 20:18.794
I'm missing, the point?

20:18.794 --> 20:21.700
I don't understand why she's
in there playing head chef.

20:21.700 --> 20:23.619
- Because we don't have anyone else!

20:23.619 --> 20:26.215
I mean, she became chef

20:26.215 --> 20:29.315
when my dad was in a car accident in 2008.

20:30.626 --> 20:33.254
- He was bedridden for about six months

20:33.254 --> 20:36.048
and then moved in to run
the hotel the next day.

20:36.048 --> 20:37.914
My mom became a chef overnight.

20:37.914 --> 20:40.928
She came to the hotel,

20:40.928 --> 20:43.483
saw where she thought she was needed

20:43.483 --> 20:45.578
and jumped in the kitchen.

20:45.578 --> 20:49.753
And ever since she's been
trying to make it work.

20:49.753 --> 20:51.876
- And so how long has it
been functioning like this?

20:51.876 --> 20:54.295
- And I think it's been in this stage

20:54.295 --> 20:57.267
for about two or three years.

20:57.267 --> 21:01.104
My dad has taken a step back
and given up a little bit.

21:01.104 --> 21:03.196
- Okay, we have to be
strong. Get some fresh air.

21:03.196 --> 21:04.139
- I am.

21:04.139 --> 21:05.125
- Get your eyes nice and bright, okay?

21:05.125 --> 21:07.673
- Okay, thanks. (chuckles)

21:07.673 --> 21:09.258
- Finally, I get it,

21:09.258 --> 21:11.584
the Hotel Chester has been in a tailspin

21:11.584 --> 21:13.200
since David's car accident.

21:13.200 --> 21:15.316
I wish Sukie or David had told me.

21:15.316 --> 21:18.712
Wow, the beer garden, interesting.

21:18.712 --> 21:21.594
Sukie is just trying to make
this work as best she can,

21:21.594 --> 21:23.470
but she's failing miserably.

21:23.470 --> 21:26.317
And David has hotel knowledge,
but since the accident

21:26.317 --> 21:27.850
he has taken a backseat.

21:27.850 --> 21:29.497
This whole place feels lost,

21:29.497 --> 21:31.531
the owners, the restaurant, the bedrooms,

21:31.531 --> 21:33.428
even this garden feels abandoned,

21:33.428 --> 21:34.711
just like the dinner guests.

21:34.711 --> 21:36.775
The customers are getting so pissed off,

21:36.775 --> 21:39.122
I'm gonna have to do
something otherwise this place

21:39.122 --> 21:40.199
is gonna go crazy.

21:43.849 --> 21:45.232
(electricity buzzes)

21:45.232 --> 21:47.588
The Hotel Chester in
Starkville, Mississippi

21:47.588 --> 21:49.757
is on the brink of financial disaster

21:49.757 --> 21:51.655
and I've finally found out why.

21:51.655 --> 21:54.032
- My dad was in a car accident in 2008.

21:54.032 --> 21:57.077
- David's car accident sent
the hotel into a sharp decline.

21:57.077 --> 21:58.631
- Oh, no!

21:58.631 --> 22:00.497
- Sukie is drowning in the kitchen,

22:00.497 --> 22:02.009
trying to keep the business afloat.

22:02.009 --> 22:03.406
How long have you actually been waiting?

22:03.406 --> 22:05.106
- I would say at least 45 minutes.

22:05.106 --> 22:06.430
- We've been here about an hour.

22:06.430 --> 22:07.299
(David yawns)

22:07.299 --> 22:10.351
- While her husband David
isn't taking the reins,

22:10.351 --> 22:11.708
I can't see the diners starve,

22:11.708 --> 22:14.668
so I've dashed over to
the local supermarket.

22:14.668 --> 22:16.409
The least I can do to help poor Sukie

22:16.409 --> 22:19.433
is to cook up a few sliders
before the customers walk out.

22:21.380 --> 22:23.895
If those diners are gonna
get any food, trust me,

22:23.895 --> 22:26.027
tonight it's coming from me.

22:26.027 --> 22:30.040
That is ridiculous in there,
an hour for appetisers, crazy.

22:32.816 --> 22:33.770
So sorry about the delay.

22:33.770 --> 22:35.424
- Oh, thank you!
- There's a little beef slider

22:35.424 --> 22:36.896
from the barbecue in the garden.

22:36.896 --> 22:38.535
I don't want you guys weltering away.

22:38.535 --> 22:39.515
Everybody got some food now?

22:39.515 --> 22:41.023
- [Dinner] Yes.
- [Gordon] Feel a bit better?

22:41.023 --> 22:41.986
- [Dinner] Yes (laughs).

22:41.986 --> 22:43.530
- The burgers have
brought Sukie enough time

22:43.530 --> 22:45.083
to get through the rest of dinner service

22:45.083 --> 22:46.661
without anyone walking out.

22:48.462 --> 22:51.986
after a long three hours,
everyone has finally been fed.

22:51.986 --> 22:54.155
I'm sure Sukie is as relieved as me

22:54.155 --> 22:55.962
that dinner service is over.

22:55.962 --> 22:57.408
(guest chattering)

22:57.408 --> 22:58.534
How are you, Sukie?

22:58.534 --> 22:59.577
- Fine, fine.
- You're fine?

22:59.577 --> 23:00.446
- Yes.

23:00.446 --> 23:02.152
- That was a tough one.

23:02.152 --> 23:03.164
- It was very tough.

23:03.164 --> 23:04.032
- [Gordon] Yeah?
- Yes sir.

23:04.032 --> 23:06.428
- Why don't you guys get
out of here, you go home?

23:06.428 --> 23:07.919
Let's hook up first
thing tomorrow morning.

23:07.919 --> 23:09.462
How far is home away from here?

23:09.462 --> 23:11.311
- This is our home now, we've got a room.

23:11.311 --> 23:13.268
- What do you mean this is your home?

23:13.268 --> 23:14.842
- We live here.

23:14.842 --> 23:15.906
- You live onsite?

23:15.906 --> 23:17.272
- Yes.

23:17.272 --> 23:18.586
- You have an apartment here?

23:18.586 --> 23:21.036
- No, right in there
there's the handicap room.

23:21.954 --> 23:23.900
That's our home now.

23:23.900 --> 23:25.989
- You live in the handicap room?

23:25.989 --> 23:26.875
- Yes.

23:26.875 --> 23:27.814
- Can you show me?

23:28.961 --> 23:32.266
- Since Dave's accident
I gave up everything.

23:32.266 --> 23:34.591
We had no money so we had no choice

23:34.591 --> 23:36.906
but to live in this room.

23:36.906 --> 23:39.438
- [Gordon] You live in here?
- [Sukie] Yes.

23:39.438 --> 23:41.483
- There's not even a fucking window!

23:41.483 --> 23:42.748
- No.

23:42.748 --> 23:45.832
- [Gordon] Sukie, I had no
idea things were this bad.

23:45.832 --> 23:48.539
- Well, have to do what you have to do.

23:48.539 --> 23:49.710
- [Gordon] I'm so sorry.

23:49.710 --> 23:54.924
- Well, you know, sometimes
you have the bad times.

23:58.313 --> 23:59.268
- Could you get David, please?

23:59.268 --> 24:00.137
- Okay.

24:01.352 --> 24:05.382
I don't know what else to
do, we have two children.

24:05.382 --> 24:08.990
I would like for them not to have to worry

24:08.990 --> 24:10.286
about their mom and dad.

24:11.910 --> 24:15.799
- Okay, so you were running this hotel,

24:15.799 --> 24:16.817
this was your baby, David?

24:16.817 --> 24:18.906
- That's right, yes.

24:18.906 --> 24:23.859
- And sadly you got involved
in a tragic car accident.

24:23.859 --> 24:25.007
- Yes.

24:25.007 --> 24:26.632
- What happened?

24:26.632 --> 24:29.552
- Legs.
- I broke both of my ankles

24:29.552 --> 24:32.058
and my back in two places.

24:34.300 --> 24:35.607
- We nearly lost him.

24:36.820 --> 24:39.114
- I mean, I was pretty busted up

24:39.114 --> 24:43.410
so I've been spending most
of the past five years

24:43.410 --> 24:44.393
just recovering.

24:46.069 --> 24:47.987
- [Gordon] why did you sell your house?

24:47.987 --> 24:50.636
- We couldn't make the payment and-

24:50.636 --> 24:52.690
- You foreclosed?
- [David] Yes.

24:52.690 --> 24:55.161
- That's terrible, I'm
sorry, I didn't know that.

24:55.161 --> 24:58.894
And you come home every
night now into this bedroom?

24:58.894 --> 25:00.458
- [David] Mm-hm.

25:00.458 --> 25:04.100
- This is awful, it is no way to live.

25:06.599 --> 25:09.980
I think you deserve something better.

25:09.980 --> 25:14.159
I promise I'm gonna help
you fix this place, okay?

