37:42.001 --> 37:43.722
Time to say goodbye.

37:43.722 --> 37:44.796
- [David] Hey Gordon.

37:44.796 --> 37:46.516
- [Gordon] I'm gonna miss you both.

37:46.516 --> 37:47.746
- We're gonna miss you too.

37:47.746 --> 37:51.323
- Look after each other,
embrace these students,

37:51.323 --> 37:55.243
their parents, and get this hotel full.

37:55.243 --> 37:57.798
When I see you behind
that bar serving pints

37:57.798 --> 37:59.352
that for me is you in your element.

37:59.352 --> 38:00.220
- All right.

38:00.220 --> 38:01.089
- Take care of yourselves, okay?

38:01.089 --> 38:01.957
- Yes sir.

38:01.957 --> 38:02.834
- Well done, darling.
(lips smacking)

38:02.834 --> 38:05.441
Seeing you bouncing
around out there tonight,

38:05.441 --> 38:08.507
happy in front of customers
rather than stressed,

38:08.507 --> 38:10.957
good to see. Take care
of yourself.(sighs) Wow.

38:11.887 --> 38:14.797
(car door slams)

38:14.797 --> 38:16.089
(upbeat dramatic music)

38:16.089 --> 38:20.779
Oh damn. I'm sorry, I've
forgot one little thing.

38:20.779 --> 38:21.942
Can you come with me, please?

38:21.942 --> 38:22.865
- Yeah.

38:22.865 --> 38:24.481
- One little thing before I go.

38:27.282 --> 38:28.488
(door shuts)

38:28.488 --> 38:29.958
(electricity buzzes)

38:29.958 --> 38:31.426
(gentle upbeat music)

38:31.426 --> 38:34.241
The re-launch of the Hotel
Chester is a huge success.

38:34.241 --> 38:35.304
Can you come with me, please?

38:35.304 --> 38:36.173
- Yeah.

38:36.173 --> 38:38.631
- Now Sukie and David are on
their way to making this hotel

38:38.631 --> 38:40.872
the talk of the town.
Get in the car, please.

38:40.872 --> 38:43.743
But before I leave, I have
one more surprise for them.

38:47.337 --> 38:49.784
There's one more little
thing I wanted to show you.

38:49.784 --> 38:53.208
Isn't this place beautiful?
That gorgeous pool there.

38:53.208 --> 38:56.503
Both of you, come in for two seconds.

38:56.503 --> 38:59.196
(upbeat music)

39:02.123 --> 39:06.898
Now, living in that tiny
room with no windows

39:06.898 --> 39:12.112
is not the way to live. So
this is your new apartment.

39:14.646 --> 39:17.628
I've rented this for the
next six months and I'm sure,

39:17.628 --> 39:20.016
when the business kicks off,
you'll have sufficient funds

39:20.016 --> 39:20.884
to rent this apartment.

39:20.884 --> 39:22.487
- Oh, I don't know what
to say. Oh, I love it!

39:22.487 --> 39:24.093
- Open plan kitchen, lounge.

39:24.093 --> 39:26.449
Have a quick look and the
bedroom through there, beautiful.

39:26.449 --> 39:28.566
- This is just what we really needed

39:28.566 --> 39:32.171
for Dave and me to getaway.

39:32.171 --> 39:33.863
- (laughs) There we go.

39:33.863 --> 39:36.365
- Oh, Dave, this is nice!

39:36.365 --> 39:37.762
- [David] Ah, this is, this is nice.

39:37.762 --> 39:40.217
- [Sukie] This is so sweet!

39:40.217 --> 39:45.431
- You need some time out.
- Thank you! Thank you!

39:45.716 --> 39:46.939
- That is yours.

39:46.939 --> 39:48.440
- Thank you so much!

39:48.440 --> 39:50.977
- Thank you, thank you
again, that's awesome.

39:51.923 --> 39:55.833
I'm just damn flabbergasted, actually.

39:55.833 --> 40:01.046
- Being onsite and not having
time out of your hotel,

40:01.630 --> 40:04.352
you were blind to the
potential on your doorstep,

40:04.352 --> 40:05.964
was ridiculous.

40:05.964 --> 40:06.832
- Thank you.

40:06.832 --> 40:08.408
We thought Gordon was just coming here

40:08.408 --> 40:13.392
to help us with the business,
he ended up helping us,

40:13.392 --> 40:15.749
emotionally, our marriage.

40:15.749 --> 40:18.752
He very much wanted for us to be together

40:18.752 --> 40:19.683
and that was so lovely.

40:19.683 --> 40:22.742
- That's pretty damn awesome,
no question about it.

40:22.742 --> 40:24.695
- Mm, really, really nice.

40:24.695 --> 40:25.564
- Yes.

40:26.730 --> 40:28.614
(both kiss)

40:28.614 --> 40:32.766
Thank you again. Now, I'm
gonna hug you too. (laughs)

40:32.766 --> 40:34.513
- This is a fantastic home.
- Take care, you, okay?

40:34.513 --> 40:38.216
- I'm gonna kiss you too. (laughs)

40:38.216 --> 40:41.941
- Spend some quality time
together, you deserve it.

40:41.941 --> 40:43.088
Goodnight and good luck.

40:43.088 --> 40:45.173
- All right, bye Gordon.
- [Gordon] Bye-bye now.

40:45.173 --> 40:46.227
(door slams)

40:46.227 --> 40:47.395
- It's a new start for me

40:47.395 --> 40:50.273
and it's definitely a new start for Sukie.

40:50.273 --> 40:52.202
- [Sukie] This is so sweet!
- [David] I'm gonna get naked

40:52.202 --> 40:53.351
in the pool right now.

40:53.351 --> 40:54.621
(Sukie laughs)

40:54.621 --> 40:58.096
- It's so nice to see
two people finally happy.

40:59.918 --> 41:04.040
Strawberries on fucking
sushi, what was she thinking?

41:07.686 --> 41:11.158
Since my visit, the Hotel
Chester's bookings have gone up.

41:11.158 --> 41:12.597
- Have y'all stayed with us before?

41:12.597 --> 41:13.595
- No, this is the first time.

41:13.595 --> 41:16.247
- And the guests are enjoying
the new improvements.

41:16.247 --> 41:18.599
- It's just not generic, run of the mill.

41:18.599 --> 41:20.814
I think this is something special now.

41:20.814 --> 41:21.962
- It does feel special.

41:21.962 --> 41:25.861
It's actually had a touch
of care given to it.

41:25.861 --> 41:26.775
(guests chattering)

41:26.775 --> 41:28.530
- [Gordon] With the new
menu and beer garden,

41:28.530 --> 41:30.970
the hotel has become a local
hit with the college kids.

41:30.970 --> 41:32.958
- I don't know what
this is but I enjoy it.

41:32.958 --> 41:35.401
- The craft beer you have?
- Uh-huh.

41:35.401 --> 41:36.517
- I mean it was outstanding, you know?

41:36.517 --> 41:37.385
- [Sukie] Was it?
- Yes,

41:37.385 --> 41:39.655
I mean, the local brewery Mississippi,

41:39.655 --> 41:41.106
plus you had a mix of everything.

41:41.106 --> 41:43.044
- Oh, so you had a sampler?

41:43.044 --> 41:44.431
- We had the sampler, it was very good.

41:44.431 --> 41:46.996
- The new buzz around town
means the Hotel Chester

41:46.996 --> 41:50.135
is now bringing in thousands
of guests every weekend,

41:50.135 --> 41:52.648
and David and Sukie are
working as a team again.

41:52.648 --> 41:56.829
- Next march 8th, we've
got booked for a reception

41:56.829 --> 41:59.467
for about 150 to 200 people so they want

41:59.467 --> 42:02.970
all of the 36 rooms for two nights.

42:02.970 --> 42:04.566
Gordon has saved us,

42:04.566 --> 42:08.199
our relationship as
husband and wife is better,

42:08.199 --> 42:10.779
we are now partners.

42:10.779 --> 42:12.432
- I wanna give you all a hug!

42:12.432 --> 42:13.385
- Come on Megan, give us a kiss.

42:13.385 --> 42:16.202
- I'm so excited.
- Come on, guys!

42:16.202 --> 42:19.935
- What Gordon has done for
us means everything to us.

42:19.935 --> 42:23.825
And I think Gordon's helped
to put the hotel on the map!

42:23.825 --> 42:24.693
Let's go suck face for a while.

42:24.693 --> 42:29.757
- 90% of the time. (laughs)

42:59.069 --> 43:00.403
- [Voice Over] One potato, two potato.

43:00.403 --> 43:03.096
(man laughing)

43:47.482 --> 43:50.610
(upbeat rock music)

44:17.676 --> 44:22.889
One potato, two potato.
